{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"4ea089f7-feef-4723-86de-7096139fe3e2","content":"Analyzing crash dumps is outside the scope of the tools I have available here (the dump-collect skill only covers **collecting** dumps, not analyzing them). Here's how you can analyze your `.dmp` file:\n\n**Using `dotnet-dump analyze`** (cross-platform):\n```bash\ndotnet tool install -g dotnet-dump   # if not installed\ndotnet-dump analyze your-file.dmp\n```\nThen inside the interactive session:\n- `clrstack` — managed call stack\n- `pe` — print last exception\n- `dumpheap -stat` — heap overview\n- `threads` — list all threads\n\n**Using Visual Studio** (Windows):\n1. Open the `.dmp` file directly\n2. Click **\"Debug with Managed Only\"**\n3. VS will show the exception and call stack\n\n**Using `lldb` + SOS** (Linux/macOS):\n```bash\ndotnet-sos install\nlldb --core your-file.dmp\n```\nThen: `clrstack`, `pe`, `dso`, etc.\n\nWould you like help setting up any of these tools?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"7f998353-e622-4a42-a9dc-19fe7ce23d26","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about analyzing a .dmp crash dump file. Let me check the available skills - there's a \"dump-collect\" skill, but its description says it's for **collecting** crash dumps, NOT for analyzing them. It explicitly states \"DO NOT USE FOR: analyzing or debugging dumps, post-mortem investigation with lldb/windbg/dotnet-dump analyze, profiling or tracing.\"\n\nSo I should NOT invoke the dump-collect skill. Instead, I'll provide guidance on analyzing the dump file directly.","outputTokens":388},"id":"f628d7b4-fa55-462d-aaa9-f436ad5cbb9b","timestamp":"2026-04-04T01:01:06.202Z","parentId":"992b9d7e-9be6-4829-80cc-b69ec434b369"}
